Assume the preprocessor processes the following lines in order. What is printed?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#ifndef MY_FLAG
#define MY_FLAG
std::cout << "defined\n";
#endif
#ifndef MY_FLAG
std::cout << "again\n";
#endif
int main() { return 0; }
```

(Note: the `cout` lines are at file scope for illustration — imagine they are inside `main`.)

What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

#define ALREADY_DEFINED

#ifndef ALREADY_DEFINED
int x = 10;
#else
int x = 42;
#endif

int main() {
    std::cout << x << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```
